Quote: [M.O.W. engineer discussing `Thermal Heating at Chateau Tongariro'.] [The thermostat] was found to be working far too frequently, the sensing device measuring the loads taken by the hotel being much too sensitive. Its sensitivity had been reduced by means of what had been nicknamed, `a Public Service relay', a slugging device which, when something happened, did nothing about it until absolutely necessary.
